"title": "5167: mouth",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5167: mouth",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In addition to its normal physical functions, it has great potential for good and evil. The words of God's mouth are always effective. Mouth is also used in the sense of an entrance or opening.</p>\n<h2>The words of God's mouth</h2>\n<h3>They are always effective</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:38\">LAM 3:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:11\">ISA 55:11</a></p>\n<h3>They are creative and life-giving</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:3\">DEU 8:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:4\">MAT 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>They bring judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:5\">HOS 6:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:30\">JOB 15:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:8\">2TH 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:16\">REV 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>They are reliable</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:19\">NUM 23:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:15\">1KI 8:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:4\">2CH 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:24\">1KI 8:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:15\">2CH 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:13-Heb6:18\">HEB 6:13–6:18</a></p>\n<h3>They are to be treasured</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:72\">PSA 119:72</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:8\">JOS 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job23:12\">JOB 23:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:13-Ps119:14\">PSA 119:13–119:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:103\">PSA 119:103</a></p>\n<h2>God puts his words into the mouths of his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:18\">DEU 18:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:12\">EXO 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:15\">EXO 4:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:38\">NUM 22:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:24\">1KI 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:2\">ISA 49:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:7\">JER 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:9\">JER 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:1-Ezek3:4\">EZK 3:1–3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:25\">ACT 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:31\">ACT 4:31</a></p>\n<h2>The mouth used for eating and drinking</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:20\">PRO 18:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:5-Judg7:6\">JDG 7:5–7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:29-Ps78:30\">PSA 78:29–78:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:24\">PRO 19:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:20\">PRO 30:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:7\">ECC 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:14\">EZK 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:12\">NAM 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:8\">ACT 11:8</a></p>\n<h2>The mouths of animals</h2>\n<h3>The danger they represent</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:35\">1SA 17:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:14\">JOB 41:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:19\">JOB 41:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:21\">JOB 41:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:12\">AMO 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Enemies described as dangerous animals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:13\">PSA 22:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:21\">PSA 22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:17\">2TI 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>God controls the mouths of dangerous animals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:22\">DAN 6:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:28-Num22:30\">NUM 22:28–22:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:33\">HEB 11:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:16\">2PE 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:15-Rev12:16\">REV 12:15–12:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:13\">REV 16:13</a></p>\n<h2>The mouth used for speaking</h2>\n<h3>To speak what is good</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:11\">PRO 10:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job16:5\">JOB 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:14\">PSA 19:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:7\">PRO 8:7</a></p>\n<h3>To praise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:8\">PSA 71:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:15\">PSA 51:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:5\">PSA 63:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:1\">PSA 89:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:6\">ROM 15:6</a></p>\n<h3>To testify about God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:15\">PSA 71:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:18\">PSA 71:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:10\">ROM 10:10</a></p>\n<h3>To teach God's wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:3\">PSA 49:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:30\">PSA 37:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:31\">PRO 10:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:6-Mal2:7\">MAL 2:6–2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:35\">MAT 13:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:2\">PSA 78:2</a></p>\n<h3>To speak what is bad</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:7\">PSA 10:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:3\">1SA 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:12\">JOB 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:9\">PSA 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps36:3\">PSA 36:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:19\">PSA 50:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:3\">PRO 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:21\">PRO 7:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:9\">PRO 11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:28\">PRO 15:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:28\">PRO 26:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:17\">ISA 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:13\">ISA 29:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:45\">LUK 6:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:5-Rev13:6\">REV 13:5–13:6</a></p>\n<h2>Gestures involving the mouth</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:1\">JOB 3:1</a> <em>Opening the mouth signifies declaration</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:5\">JOB 21:5</a> <em>Clapping the hand over the mouth signifies keeping silent from fear or astonishment</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:2\">ACT 23:2</a> <em>Striking the mouth signifies rebuke.</em></p>\n<h2>God fills mouths</h2>\n<h3>With good things</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:10\">PSA 81:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>With joy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps126:2\">PSA 126:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:13\">EZR 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:21\">JOB 8:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:10\">JOB 35:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:3\">PSA 40:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:16\">PSA 132:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:6\">PSA 149:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:6\">ISA 35:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:64\">LUK 1:64</a></p>\n<h3>With food</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:15\">PSA 145:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:20\">NEH 9:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:27-Ps78:30\">PSA 78:27–78:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:16\">PSA 81:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:27-Ps104:28\">PSA 104:27–104:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:53\">LUK 1:53</a></p>\n<h2>Mouth meaning entrance or opening</h2>\n<h3>The mouth of a well</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:2-Gen29:3\">GEN 29:2–29:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:8-Gen29:10\">GEN 29:8–29:10</a></p>\n<h3>The mouth of a sack</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:27\">GEN 42:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:12\">GEN 43:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:21\">GEN 43:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:1-Gen44:2\">GEN 44:1–44:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:8\">GEN 44:8</a></p>\n<h3>The mouth of the grave</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:7\">PSA 141:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:14\">ISA 5:14</a> <em>“the grave” is literally “Sheol”, the shadowy abode of the departed.</em></p>\n<h3>The mouth of a cave</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:18\">JOS 10:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:22\">JOS 10:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:27\">JOS 10:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:13\">1KI 19:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:28\">JER 48:28</a></p>\n<h3>The mouth of a river</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:5\">JOS 15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:19\">JOS 18:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:7\">ISA 19:7</a></p>\n<h3>The mouth of the earth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:11\">GEN 4:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:30\">NUM 16:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:32\">NUM 16:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:10\">NUM 26:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:6\">DEU 11:6</a></p>\n<h2>Mouth likened to a sword</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:15\">JOB 5:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:2\">ISA 49:2</a></p>",
